[l] Old and busted: Remote Code Execution in Windows via SMB.New hotness: Remote Code Execution in Unix via SMB.All versions of Samba from 3.5.0 onwards are vulnerable to a remote code execution vulnerability, allowing a malicious client to upload a shared library to a writable share, and then cause the server to load and execute it.Und da muss man noch nicht mal irgendwelche Offsets raten oder so. So schoen stabile Exploits gibt es selten!
